text: A processed pork meat food product is defined as something that lies at the intersection of processed meat food products and pork meat food products. It is a type of both processed meat food product and pork meat food product.

A spice or herb is a type of plant food product and also falls under the category of a condiment food product. It is defined as a vegetable product, including leaves, flowers, seeds, and roots, that is rich in essential oils and aromatic principles, primarily used as a condiment. Furthermore, it has exact synonyms, which are "herb and spice" as well as "herb or spice."
An animal lipid food product is both a type of lipid food product and a type of animal food product.
Coffee beverage is a type of coffee-based beverage product and is defined as a brewed drink prepared from roasted seeds, commonly called coffee beans, of the coffee plant.
Tea beverage liquid is a type of tea-based beverage product, defined as a beverage prepared from the cured leaves of Camellia sinensis by combination with hot or boiling water.
hot chocolate food product is a type of nonfermented plant derived beverage product.
mate food product is a type of nonfermented plant derived beverage product.

A fish food product is categorized as a type of vertebrate animal food product. It is defined as including products made from any fish species, characterized as aquatic vertebrates with gills and fins.
A fish egg food product is both a type of egg food product and a type of fish product from an unspecified species.
avian food product is a type of vertebrate animal food product.
An animal-derived beverage is both a type of animal food product and a type of beverage food product.
A plant-derived beverage is both a type of plant food product and a type of beverage food product.

A plant-derived fermented beverage is both a type of fermented beverage and a type of plant-derived beverage. It represents the intersection of fermented beverages and plant-derived beverages, meaning it shares characteristics of both categories.
nonfermented plant derived beverage product is a type of plant derived beverage.

A dairy food product is a type of vertebrate animal food product defined as having mammalian milk or a milk component as an ingredient. Additionally, it is synonymously known as a dairy product and a milk product.
milk or milk based food product is a type of dairy food product.
Fermented food is a type of multi-component food product and is also a type of food product created by a process.
non fruit wine food product is a type of wine or wine like food product.

Beer beverage is a type of fermented grain beverage and is defined as a fermented cereal beverage resulting from the fermentation most commonly of malted barley, though wheat, corn, or rice may be included, by a yeast, most commonly Saccharomyces cerevisiae. It is flavored by dried flowers of hops, Humulus lupulus.

A vegetable food product is a type of plant food product, defined as any plant food product which, typically, is constituted by intact parts from one or more annual plants cultivated as field and garden crops in the open and under glass, and used almost exclusively for food.
botanical fruit food product is a type of plant food product.

A legume food product is identified as a type of botanical fruit food product and is defined as a one-celled fruit (pod) usually dehiscing down both sutures, with the seed attached along a ventral suture, as per Roubik 1995. It is exactly synonymous with "legume." Additionally, it has narrow synonyms identified by the URLs http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FOODON_03411254 and http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FOODON_03411338.
Camel milk beverage is a type of camelid dairy food product and also a type of camelid milk beverage.
Zebra milk beverage is a type of zebra dairy food product as well as a type of equine milk beverage.
egg food product is a type of vertebrate animal food product.
A hen egg food product is a type of avian egg food product defined as any food product consisting mainly of hen eggs or derivatives.

Apple cider alcoholic is a type of fermented apple beverage, which is defined as Cider, hard apple cider, or hard cider in the US, being an alcoholic beverage made from the fermented juice of apples. Additionally, it has the exact synonym "cider".
orange juice unpasteurized  is a type of orange juice liquid.
cake food product is a type of bakery food product.
cake icing food product is a type of dessert food.
Chocolate food product is a type of confectionery and also falls under the category of chocolate or cocoa.

The custard dessert food product is a type of food that is cooked and specifically falls under the category of cow milk desserts. It is defined as a food that involves a mixture of whipped and cooked milk, sugar, and egg yolks. Additionally, it is precisely known by the exact synonym "sweet custard."

Ground beef food product is a type of beef food product defined as a ground beef product made of beef that has been finely chopped with a knife or a meat grinder (American English) or mincing machine (British English). Ground beef is utilized in numerous recipes including hamburgers and spaghetti Bolognese. It is represented by the image 631px-hackfleisch-1.jpg. Moreover, ground beef food product is exactly synonymous with beef mince, ground beef, hamburger meat, and minced beef.

A poultry food product is a type of avian food product, defined as a food product from a category of domestic birds kept for meat, eggs, and feathers. This category includes fowl such as chickens, turkeys, and waterfowls such as domestic ducks and geese, as well as other meat birds like pigeons and doves and game birds including pheasants.
duck meat food product is a type of poultry meat food product.
goose meat food product is a type of poultry meat food product.
Turkey meat food product, a type of poultry meat food product, is defined as any food product made predominantly of turkey parts.

Cantaloupe, also identified as a type of muskmelon (Cucumis melo) in the Cucurbitaceae family, is known by various names worldwide. In India and the United States, it's called muskmelon; in Australia and New Zealand, it's referred to as rockmelon; in South Africa, it's known as spanspek; and in Scotland, it's called capuchin. Additionally, it has exact synonyms such as cantaloup and muskmelon.
potato salad food product is a type of plant based salad food product.
Salad dressing is a type of condiment and plant product dressing, defined as a sauce for a salad.
clam food product is a type of mollusc food product.
oyster food product is a type of mollusc food product.
Shellfish food product is a type of animal seafood product and also a type of invertebrate animal food product.
goat milk cheese unpasteurized  is a type of goat milk cheese food product.
Pecorino cheese, a food product, is a type of sheep milk cheese defined as a family of hard Italian cheeses made from sheep milk.
sheep milk cheese unpasteurized  is a type of sheep milk cheese food product.
unpasteurized camel milk beverage is a type of camel milk beverage.
apple condiment is a type of condiment food product.
apple food product is a type of pomaceous fruit food product.

Apple vinegar food product is the same as something that intersects between vinegar food products and apple food products. It is a type of vinegar food product, a type of apple condiment, and also a type of apple food product.
bakery food product is a type of food product by process.
Barley flour food product is the same as something that intersects between flour food product and barley food product. It is a type of flour food product and also a type of barley food product.

Bean food product is both a type of legume food product and a plant seed vegetable food product. Additionally, it is defined as a human or animal food product, such as a snap, shell, or dry bean product, derived from the fruit pod, seed, or leaf of one of several genera of the flowering plant family Fabaceae.
berry food product is a type of plant fruit food product.
A broad bean food product is a type of bean food product, defined as a product derived from the broad bean plant.

Cabbage juice food product is the same as something that is an intersection of cabbage food products and vegetable juice food products. Additionally, it is a type of cabbage food product and also a type of vegetable juice food product.
Cattle cured meat food product is the same as something that is both a cured meat food product and a beef food product. It is a type of cured meat food product and also a type of beef food product.

A food product component is a type of food product defined as a food product that typically serves as an ingredient in another food product rather than being consumed on its own, and it is more complex than a chemical food component.

A cocoa beverage is defined as something that is both a plant-derived beverage and a cocoa food product. Additionally, a cocoa beverage is a type of plant-derived beverage and also a type of cocoa food product.
common bean food product is a type of bean food product.
A cow milk-based food product is a type of cattle dairy food product and is also classified as a type of milk or milk-based food product.
Cow milk dessert is a type of food product that is based on cow milk and falls under the category of milk desserts.
cowpea vegetable food product is a type of vegetable food product.
A dairy dessert food product is both a type of dairy food product and a type of dessert food.
fermented cereal beverage is a type of plant derived fermented beverage.
food flavoring or seasoning product is a type of food product component.
Flaxseed food product, which is a type of plant seed food product, has an exact synonym: linseed food product.
food dressing product is a type of food product component.

Frozen dairy dessert is the same as something that is both a dairy dessert food product and a frozen dairy food product. Additionally, frozen dairy dessert is classified as a type of dairy dessert food product and also as a type of frozen dairy food product.
frozen dairy food product is a type of dairy food product.

Fruit salad food product is the same as something that intersects both plant fruit food products and plant-based salad food products. Moreover, it is a type of both plant fruit food product and plant-based salad food product.
grain based vinegar food product is a type of vinegar food product.
A leguminous vegetable food product is a type of legume food product, defined as a food product made from legumes that are considered vegetables, such as immature raw legume pods or seeds.
Lupine bean food product is a type of bean food product and has the exact synonym lupin.
melon food product is a type of cucurbit fruit food product.
milk dessert food product is a type of dairy dessert food product.
millet food product is a type of cereal grain food product.
A mollusc food product is a type of shellfish food product and it is exactly synonymous with mollusk food product.
mustard food product is a type of brassica food product.
orange food product is a type of citrus fruit food product.

The pigeon pea vegetable food product is a type of leguminous vegetable food product, pigeon pea food product, and pea food product. It is defined as a product containing primarily immature ripe pigeon peas.

A plant-based bakery food product is the same as something that falls into the intersection of a bakery food product and a multi-component plant food product. This means that a plant-based bakery food product is simultaneously a type of bakery food product and a type of multi-component plant food product.

Plant-based candy is identical to something that is both a candy food product and a multi-component plant food product. It is a type of candy food product and also a type of multi-component plant food product.
plant based refined or partially refined food product is a type of refined or partially refined food product.
A plant-based salad food product is both a type of salad food product and a type of multi-component plant food product.

Plant fat or oil refined food products are a type of plant lipid and plant-based refined or partially refined food products. These products are defined as edible plant fats or oils with characteristics that consumers desire, including a bland flavor and odor, clear appearance, light color, stability to oxidation, and suitability for frying. These desired characteristics are the result of a refining process that removes free fatty acids.

A plant fruit, when categorized as a vegetable food product, is a type of plant fruit food product defined as a plant fruit food product that, either in common language or by regulation, is labeled as a vegetable food product.

A plant product dressing is the same as something that is both a food dressing product and a multi-component plant food product. Additionally, it is classified as a type of food dressing product and a type of multi-component plant food product.

A plant seed based bakery food product is the same as something that is both a plant seed food product and a plant-based bakery food product. Additionally, a plant seed based bakery food product is a type of plant seed food product and also a type of plant-based bakery food product.
The plant seed vegetable food product is a type of both plant seed food product and vegetable food product.

A plant stem or spear vegetable food product is defined as something that falls into the intersection category of both plant stem food products and vegetable food products. Additionally, this food product is identified as a type of plant stem food product and also as a type of vegetable food product.
plant sweetener is a type of sweetener food product.
Food preserved is a type of food product that is preserved by a process, and it is broadly synonymous with preserved food.
organ meat product is a type of meat whole or parts.

A prepared hen egg product is defined as a product predominantly made of hen egg that has been cooked and may only require defrosting or reheating for consumption. It is the same as something that is both a prepared food product and a hen egg food product. Additionally, a prepared hen egg product is a type of prepared food product as well as a type of hen egg food product.
refined or partially refined food product is a type of processed food product.
salad food product is a type of prepared food product.
soft cheese food product is a type of cow milk cheese.
soybean condiment is a type of condiment food product.
soybean seed field food product is a type of edible seed food product.

A soybean food product is a type of bean food product and also a type of soybean seed field food product. It is defined as a product derived from the soybean plant and has the exact synonym "soy product."
steeped beverage product is a type of plant derived beverage.

Sweetener food products are types of condiment food products and also types of food flavoring or seasoning products. Additionally, the term "sweetener food product" has been replaced by the term available at http://www.langual.org/langual_thesaurus.asp?termid=H0202.

Pork cured meat food product is the same as something that intersects between pork meat food product and cured meat food product. It is a type of cured meat food product, as well as a type of processed pork meat food product.
Tomato juice food product is a type of both tomato food product and vegetable juice food product, indicating it shares the same characteristics as something that intersects both categories.
Vegetable pickle food product is a type of food that is pickled and is also a type of vegetable food product.
wine or wine like food product is a type of fermented beverage.

Food product by meal type is categorized as a type of food product and it is defined as follows: A meal type refers to the name of an eating occasion that may encompass location, food type, or other customary contextual features, according to Damion's first draft definition.
A food product by organism is a type of food product that is defined as a food product consisting of food material derived primarily from a single organism.

Food material is a type of environmental material and is defined as any substance that can be consumed by an organism to satisfy nutritional or other health needs, or to provide a social or organoleptic food experience. Additionally, food material is exactly synonymous with the terms food, foodstuff, nourishment, and sustenance.
agave food product is a type of plant food product.

A multi-component honey product is identical to something that lies at the intersection of a honey food product and a multi-component food product. Additionally, a multi-component honey product is classified as a type of honey food product and, simultaneously, as a type of multi-component food product.

A food product by quality is a type of food product that is defined as a class containing food product categories qualified by qualities such as granularity or temperature. This is particularly useful for tasks like food inspection where there might be little prior knowledge about the food's production process. Terms like "food (frozen)" serve both as quality descriptors and as outputs of a process.
Baked food is a type of food cooked and has the exact synonyms "baked" and "baked food product."

A multi-component food product is a type of food product that is defined as a food product consisting of food material derived from ingredients sourced from multiple organisms. It is also known as multi-ingredient.

Dehydrated food is a type of food that is preserved, and it is defined as a preserved food where the moisture levels in the food product have been reduced to low levels to improve shelf life. Additionally, dehydrated food is also known as dessicated food.
A food product by process is a type of food product, defined as a food product organized by the process from which it results.
pork food product is a type of swine food product.

A lipid food product is a type of extract, concentrate, or isolate of plant or animal. It is defined as a food product made primarily of plant or animal fat or oil. Additionally, it has exact synonyms such as "fats and oils" and "oils and fats."

A whole dried bean, which is the same as something that intersects something that is a whole bean and dried food, is a type of whole bean as well as a type of dried food. Its definition is that a whole dried bean is a bean resulting from natural or mechanical air drying applied to a bean or bean pod. Moreover, it has an exact synonym: dried bean.
Bean whole is a type of bean food product, defined as a seed of a bean plant from one of several genera of the flowering plant family (Fabaceae). Moreover, it is exactly synonymous with "bean."

Cooked beans are the same as something that intersects food cooked and bean substance, indicating they belong to both categories. Specifically, cooked beans are a type of food cooked and also a type of bean substance. Furthermore, cooked beans are defined as the bean material output of a cooking process applied to dry, rehydrated, or raw (fresh) beans.
Jack bean whole is a type of bean whole and also a type of jack bean food product. It is defined as a seed of a jack seed plant (Canavalia ensiformis) and has the exact synonym "jack bean."
jack bean food product is a type of bean food product.
A pigeon pea food product is a type of legume food product, defined as a food product derived from the pigeon pea plant.
Pigeon pea whole is a type of pigeon pea vegetable food product, which is defined as a seed of a pigeon pea plant (Cajanus cajan). Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with pigeon pea.

Velvet bean whole is a type of bean whole and is also a type of velvet bean food product. It is defined as a seed of a velvet bean plant (Mucuna pruriens). Furthermore, it has exact synonyms such as tericopelo bean and velvet bean.
vetch food product is a type of plant seed vegetable food product.
Vetch seed whole is a type of vetch food product, defined as a seed of a vetch plant, and is exactly synonymous with vetch seed.
pea food product is a type of legume food product.
A liver food product is a type of organ meat product, defined as a food product that derives from one or more liver organs.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:brassica_food_product rdfs:subClassOf :cruciferous_food_product,
        :vegetable_food_product ;
    :has_definition "A genus of plants in the mustard family (Brassicaceae). The members of the genus are informally known as cruciferous vegetables, cabbages, or mustard plants."@en ;
    :has_narrow_synonym "bok choy vegetable food product"@en,
        "bomdong vegetable food product"@en,
        "broccolini vegetable food product"@en,
        "chinese cabbage vegetable food product"@en,
        "choy sum vegetable food product"@en,
        "collard greens vegetable food product"@en,
        "gai lan vegetable food product"@en,
        "komatsuna vegetable food product"@en,
        "mizuna vegetable food product"@en,
        "rutabaga vegetable food product"@en,
        "savoy cabbage vegetable food product"@en,
        "tatsoi vegetable food product"@en ;
    :has_related_synonym "cole crop vegetable food product"@en,
        "cruciferous vegetable food product"@en .
text: Brassica food products are a type of vegetable and cruciferous food product, defined as a genus of plants in the mustard family (Brassicaceae). The members of this genus are informally known as cruciferous vegetables, cabbages, or mustard plants. They include a variety of narrow synonyms such as bok choy, bomdong, broccolini, Chinese cabbage, choy sum, collard greens, gai lan, komatsuna, mizuna, rutabaga, savoy cabbage, and tatsoi. Additionally, brassica food products are related to cole crops and are also known as cruciferous vegetables.
multi component wheat food product is a type of multi component plant food product.
Velvet bean food product is a type of bean food product, defined as a bean food product made from velvet bean.
An animal food product is a type of food product by an organism, defined as a food product deriving from one or more animals.
sugar granulated  is a type of sugar refined.
orange juice is a type of orange fruit beverage.

Broad Bean Whole is a type of broad bean food product and also falls under the category of bean whole. It is defined as the seed of a broad bean plant (Vicia faba). Broad Bean Whole is known by several exact synonyms, including Windsor bean, broad bean, broadbean, faba bean, and fava bean. Additionally, it has narrow synonyms such as Horse bean, field bean, tic bean, and tick bean.
vegetable juice food product is a type of plant derived beverage.
A bean substance is a type of bean food product, defined as a substance made by processing seeds from a bean plant.
A beverage food product is a type of food product categorized by meal type and is defined as a liquid prepared for consumption or a product that can be combined with water or milk to make one.
animal derived food is a type of animal food product.
Dehydrated beef is the same as something that is both a beef food product and a dehydrated food. It is a type of beef food product as well as a type of dehydrated food.
Dessert food is a type of food product categorized by meal type, and it has exact synonyms including desert preparation and dessert.
A cultured dairy product is a type of fermented dairy food product, defined as a fermented dairy product in which a microbial starter was introduced to the fermentation process.
edible seed food product is a type of plant seed food product.
Honey blend table syrup is the same as something that is both a plant sweetener and a multi-component honey product. It is a type of plant sweetener and also a type of multi-component honey product.
sugar refined  is a type of sugar product.
food dried  is a type of food dehydrated.
Fermented bean product is a type of food that is both fermented and a type of bean food product.
oil is a type of lipid food product.
processed food product is a type of food product.
Dehydrated pork is the same as something that is both a pork meat food product and a dehydrated food. It is a type of pork meat food product and also a type of dehydrated food.
mammalian milk product is a type of milk or milk based food product.

A fish product of an unspecified species is categorized as a type of fish food product. It is defined as a product, whether homemade, commercially produced, or available at retail or wholesale, that contains significant amounts of freshwater or saltwater fish and/or shellfish flesh. It is important to note that items mentioning a specific species of fish or shellfish should be excluded from this category.
cocoa food product is a type of chocolate or cocoa.
Juice beverage is a type of beverage food product and has the exact synonym "juice".

Sausage whole is a type of sausage food product, which is defined as a highly seasoned minced meat food product that is encased in a skin in the shape of a cylinder. It is also exactly synonymous with sausage.
Pate is a type of processed meat food product and is also a type of animal-derived food.
herbal infusion is a type of steeped beverage product.
sugar product is a type of plant sweetener.
multi component plant food product is a type of multi component food product.
A vegetable fat food product is a type of plant fat or oil refined food product, which is also a type of vegetable fat or oil.

Meat, whether whole or in parts, is categorized as a type of mammalian meat food product. It is defined as a product characterized by the form of or processing done to its meat component, which can be a skeletal meat part of an animal or crustacean.

Cheese or cheese product as defined by the US CFR is a type of dairy product. It is described as natural cheese, whether cured or uncured, a further processed cheese product, or a cheese product analog.

Fruit or fruit product US CFR is categorized as a type of fruit or vegetable product under US CFR. It is defined as fruit in all forms, which encompasses fruit juices and fruit juice drinks, fruit butters, jellies, preserves, and related products. Additionally, it is also synonymous with pie filling, fruit.

Milk or milk product analog as defined by the US CFR is a type of milk or milk product. It is described as a food product that possesses functional characteristics similar to milk or milk products, including cream product analogs, margarine, and milk analogs. This definition highlights that certain alternate ingredients are substituted for those components that are responsible for specific functional properties.

Milk or milk product as per the US CFR is a type of dairy product. It is defined as milk in all forms, milk-based beverage, cultured milk product, or milk or milk product analog. Additionally, the index infant formula is categorized under "MEAL REPLACEMENT."

Fruit butter, jelly, preserve, or related product, as defined by the US Code of Federal Regulations (CFR), is a type of fruit or fruit product. According to the 21 CFR 150, it is described as a semisolid or jelled food prepared from fruit or fruit juice along with other ingredients prescribed for the individual products.

Dairy product US CFR is categorized under the U.S. Code of Federal Regulations Title 21 as a type of food product. It is defined as milk, a product derived from milk, or a dairy product analog; this category includes cheese and frozen dairy desserts, according to the FDA CFSAN 1995.

Natural cheese, as defined by the US CFR, is a type of cheese or cheese product. It is made from milk or milk components, such as cream, through a specific process that involves producing curd by coagulating milk using bacterial action, enzymes, or acidification and then draining the whey. If the cheese is to be cured, the curd undergoes a curing process. This definition excludes cheese products that are made through further processing, such as comminuting, which refers to the *CHEESE PRODUCT* category.

Confectionery, as defined by the U.S. Code of Federal Regulations Title 21, is a food product type that includes candy or other food products made with sweeteners and often contains nuts, fruits, starches, flavorings, and other foods, as per 21 CFR 170.3(n)(9) [FDA CFSAN 1995].

Candy, as defined by the United States Code of Federal Regulations (US CFR), is a type of confectionery. It is a food product prepared by heating a mixture of sweeteners and other optional ingredients according to the specific formula for each subgroup.

Fruit jelly, as defined by the US CFR, is a type of fruit butter, jelly preserve, or related product. It is a jelled product made from one or more fruit juices along with optional ingredients. This category encompasses both fruit jelly, which may be sweetened with nutritive carbohydrate sweeteners (according to 21 CFR 150.140), and artificially sweetened fruit jelly (as per 21 CFR 150.141). To meet the standards, the finished fruit jelly must contain no less than 65% soluble solid content. Moreover, in the starting mixture, the ratio by weight of the fruit ingredient to the sweetener must be no less than 45:55. For artificially sweetened fruit jelly, it is required that no less than 55% of its weight consists of fruit ingredients.
Fudge, as defined in the US CFR, is a type of soft candy that is prepared by boiling milk, sugar, salt, and optional ingredients to the soft-ball stage (238 degrees F.).

Margarine, as defined by the US CFR, is an analog of butter products. It is described as a food product that shares functional characteristics similar to butter. This product can be found in either plastic form or as a liquid emulsion. It is required to contain not less than 80% fat, which may originate from vegetable sources, rendered animal carcass fats, or a mixture of these, along with other optional ingredients specified by 21 CFR 166.110.

A fruit or vegetable product as defined by the U.S. Code of Federal Regulations (CFR) falls under Title 21, which pertains to food product types. Specifically, according to the FDA's Center for Food Safety and Applied Nutrition (CFSAN) in 1995, a fruit or vegetable product encompasses fruits and vegetables in all their forms.

The USA agency food product type is categorized under the agency food product type, which is defined as a food group that includes items with common consumption, functional, or manufacturing characteristics. Examples of such items are fruit or vegetable products, dairy products, confectionary, and prepared food products, according to the FDA CFSAN 1995.
Soft candy US CFR is a type of candy US CFR and is defined as candy prepared by cooking a mixture of water, sugars, and optional ingredients to a temperature of 250 degrees F or less.

Butter product analog US CFR is a type of milk or milk product analog according to US CFR. It is defined as a food product having functional characteristics similar to a butter product; it may also be nutritionally equivalent or inferior to the product it aims to resemble. Furthermore, it is known by several synonyms including butter substitute, butter imitation, and imitation butter.
The International Agency Food Product Type is a category of Agency Food Product Type. It was defined as "Renamed from *PRODUCT TYPE, CODEX ALIMENTARIUS* in LanguaL 2008."
european union agency food product type is a type of agency food product type.
The agency food product type is a class of food product defined by an agency or consortium, which falls under the category of food material.

The Codex Alimentarius classification of food and feed commodities is recognized as an international agency food product type, having its definition detailed in Codex Alimentarius, Volume 2 - 1993, Section 2, specifically addressing Pesticide Residues in Food. This classification system was developed by the Codex Committee on Pesticide Residues and officially adopted during the 18th Session of the Codex Alimentarius Commission in 1989. It encompasses both food commodities and animal feedstuffs, noting that Codex maximum residue limits may not always be established for each. Designed to be a comprehensive listing, the Classification organizes food commodities into groups based on their similar potential for pesticide residues. Beyond its primary purpose, the Classification serves additional roles, such as aiding in setting maximum levels for other residues or contaminants in food. It is crucial for obtaining precise descriptions of food or animal feed commodities, particularly when Codex maximum residue limits are applicable to specific groups. Ultimately, the Codex Classification aims to facilitate harmonization in terms and approaches used to describe commodities subject to maximum residue limits, enabling the establishment of common group maximum residue limits for commodities with similar residue potential.
a primary food commodities of plant origin ccpr  is a type of codex alimentarius classification of food and feed commodities.

Type 2 Vegetables are a category of primary food commodities of plant origin. They are defined as foods derived from various kinds of plants, mostly annual and typically cultivated, and are recognized traditionally as "vegetables." In some countries, certain commodities cultivated over large areas are categorized as "field crops" or arable crops, for instance, sugar beet. For simplicity, in this guide, such crops are classified under Type 2 Vegetables. The exposure to pesticides in vegetables depends on the specific part of the plant consumed and the cultivation practices. Vegetables can be eaten whole or partially and come in fresh, dried, or processed forms.

015 pulses vd ccpr is a type of 02 vegetables ccpr and has a definition stating that pulses are derived from the mature seeds, whether naturally or artificially dried, of leguminous plants known as dry beans and dry peas. The seeds within the pods are usually shielded from the majority of pesticides used during the growing season, except for those pesticides that exhibit systemic action. However, the dried beans and peas are often subjected to post-harvest treatments. These dry pulses are typically consumed after processing or household cooking.
eurofir food classification is a type of european union agency food product type.

Eurofir food classification categorizes "seafood or related product eurofir" as a type. This group encompasses marine or freshwater fish, molluscs, crustaceans, and other fauna like reptiles, insects, or frogs that are not classified under the "Meats" group. Additionally, it includes seafood product analogs, seafood-based sausage or luncheon meat, and other products such as squid ink and clam juice.

Seafood product eurofir is a type of seafood or related product eurofir, which is defined as a food product whose predominant constituent is fish. This includes fish offal, dried and salted fish, smoked fish, canned fish, pickled fish, restructured fish and fish analogues, surimi, fish paste, and pâté.
Beverage non-milk EuroFIR is classified under the EuroFIR food classification as a type. It is defined as an alcoholic or non-alcoholic beverage that excludes milk and milk-based beverages.

Eurofir is a type of non-alcoholic beverage that falls under the category of beverages excluding milk. It is defined as a beverage containing no more than 0.5% alcohol, which may be flavoured, sweetened, or carbonated. This includes soft drinks and steeped beverages but excludes milk in all its forms, as well as fruit and vegetable juices.

Coffee, tea, cocoa, or infusion, as categorized by EuroFIR, is a type of non-alcoholic beverage. This category is defined as a beverage prepared by extracting flavor and other components from food sources through percolation and/or immersion in water, typically at near-boiling temperatures. It encompasses a variety of drinks including coffee (for instance, instant coffee and coffee and chicory essence), tea, herbal tea (such as green tea, black tea, tisane), cocoa beverage, and beverage powder. Moreover, this category is also known by synonyms such as infusion and steeped beverage.
The miscellaneous food product Eurofir is classified under the Eurofir food classification and is defined as EFG group 32, Eurocode-2 group 12.

Prepared food product Eurofir is categorized as a type of miscellaneous food product Eurofir. It is defined as a subgroup that encompasses multicomponent meals, sauces, retail salads, desserts, soups, snacks, and other foods where the similarity of the product type is more significant than the source of the principal ingredient(s). Additionally, prepared food product Eurofir is synonymously referred to as soup, sauce, or miscellaneous food product.

Soup Eurofir is a type of prepared food product according to Eurofir. It is defined as a liquid food made by simmering meat, poultry, seafood, or vegetables, which can be either clear or thickened to the consistency of a thin puree or may have milk or cream added. Additionally, it often contains pieces of solid food such as meat, shellfish, pasta, or vegetables, taking precedence over other food products. Examples of soup include egg and lemon soup, oxtail soup, fish soup, rice soup, lentil soup, minestrone, and cherry soup.

The GS1 Global Product Classification (GPC) is classified as a type of international agency food product type. It is defined as The Global System 1 (GS1) Global Product Classification (GPC), which is a system designed to provide buyers and sellers globally with a common language for categorizing products consistently across the world. Furthermore, the GS1 GPC classification within facet A has been updated according to the June 2017 release of the GS1 GPC Standard for Food/Beverage/Tobacco, with the exception of codes related to tobacco. For more details, one may refer to the GS1 website at [https://www.gs1.org/standards/gpc].
50220000 cereal grain pulse products gs1 gpc  is a type of gs1 global product classification gpc.
50221200 processed cereal products gs1 gpc  is a type of 50220000 cereal grain pulse products gs1 gpc.
50190000 prepared preserved foods gs1 gpc  is a type of gs1 global product classification gpc.
50192900 pasta noodles gs1 gpc  is a type of 50190000 prepared preserved foods gs1 gpc.

The U.S. Code of Federal Regulations Title 21 food product type is classified under the agency type specific to the USA and is defined as "Food and Drugs" in Title 21 of the Code of Federal Regulations. Additionally, this classification originates from the original food classification in LanguaL.
polysaccharide producing plant is a type of carbohydrate producing plant.
plant used for producing extract or concentrate is a type of whole plant.
starch producing plant is a type of polysaccharide producing plant.
carbohydrate producing plant is a type of plant used for producing extract or concentrate.
The devil's tongue plant is a type of starch-producing plant. It is also known by several synonyms, including Amorphophallus konjac, Amorphophallus rivieri, Hydrosme rivieri, and leopard palm.
The konjac plant is a type of devil's tongue plant and has the synonym Amorphophallus rivieri var. konjac.

Sugar is a type of carbohydrate, specifically an extract, concentrate, or isolate. It is defined as a broad term encompassing nutritive sweeteners such as dextrose, fructose, galactose, lactose, maltose, and sucrose. These are simple carbohydrates whose molecules are composed of one or two saccharide units. It's important to note that when 'sugar' is mentioned on a product label or in a recipe, it specifically refers to sucrose and should be indexed as such. The term 'sugar' should only be used broadly if the specific type of sugar used is not known or not listed in the vocabulary.

A carbohydrate extract concentrate or isolate, which is a type of extract, concentrate, or isolate derived from plant or animal sources, is defined as an extract, concentrate, or isolate high in sugar, oligosaccharides, or polysaccharides.
Brown sugar is a type of sugar condiment and is granulated. It is defined as soft sugar whose crystals are covered by a film of refined dark syrup, which imparts color, flavor, and moisture.

An extract, concentrate, or isolate of plant or animal is categorized as a type of food product component. This component is defined as a physical-chemical substance that has been separated from the food source or its parts through various methods such as extraction, centrifugation, filtration, heat processing, expressing, or a similar process. After separation, this component may undergo further processing to convert it into a final substance, which is then indexed. If the component is extracted using water, it might remain in an aqueous dispersion. Notably, the extract, concentrate, or isolate is indexed based on preference over the anatomic part from which it is derived. For instance, peanut oil is indexed under "PEANUT" combined with "FAT OR OIL" rather than "SEED OR KERNEL". However, fruit and vegetable juices are an exception; they can be indexed under "FRUIT JUICE OR NECTAR" or "VEGETABLE JUICE" as a product type, indicating that the anatomic part of the plant should be indexed in these cases.

Mammalian milk whey is a type of mammalian milk product, defined as the serum or watery part of milk that is separated from the thicker or more coagulable part or curd, especially in the process of making cheese; it contains lactose, minerals, and lactalbumin. Additionally, mammalian milk whey is exactly synonymous with whey.
Seed oil, a type of vegetable oil food product, is defined as the oil produced by pressing or extracting lipids from plant seeds, such as grapeseed oil, rapeseed oil, and linseed oil.

Food liquid low viscosity is a type of food liquid that is defined as a liquid that flows very easily at room temperature. Examples of low viscosity liquids include water, apple juice, sherry, acidophilus milk, whipping cream, and some heavy liqueurs. The range of low viscosity liquid spans sucrose solutions between 0 and 45% solids, with a viscosity range from 1 to 10 centipoise. When discussing this type of food liquid, the term 'solid pieces' is preferred over 'small particles' if both terms are applicable. Additionally, food liquid low viscosity is synonymous with terms such as liquid and thin.

Food liquid is a type of food product characterized by its quality. It is defined as a state of matter that exists between a solid and a gas, in which a substance possesses the ability to flow and takes the shape of its container. The viscosity of liquids can range from that of water to honey, corresponding to a viscosity range from 1 to 500 centipoise. Viscosity is an indicator of a liquid's resistance to flow. Products that can be poured but exhibit higher viscosity are referred to as semiliquid. Furthermore, food liquid is also known by its synonym, fluid.

A plant seed or nut food product is equivalent to any item that is either a nut food product or a plant seed food product. It falls under the broader category of plant food products. Additionally, the alternative term for a plant seed or nut food product is "nut or seed added."

Chocolate or cocoa is synonymous with the union of chocolate food products and cocoa food products, and it is a type of cacao food product. Additionally, an alternative term added for chocolate or cocoa is "chocolate or cocoa."

Vegetable fat or oil is the same as the union of a vegetable oil food product and a vegetable fat food product, indicating that it encompasses both categories. It is classified as a type of plant lipid food product. Furthermore, vegetable fat or oil is defined as a fat or oil derived from vegetable material, and it is also known by an alternative term, which is vegetable fat or oil added.

System process is a type of multicellular organismal process and is defined as a multicellular organismal process carried out by any of the organs or tissues in an organ system, where an organ system is a regularly interacting or interdependent group of organs or tissues that work together to carry out a biological objective. Additionally, system process has the exact synonym "organ system process."
generation of precursor metabolites and energy is a type of cellular metabolic process.
nitrogen compound metabolic process is a type of metabolic process.

Excretion is a type of system process that is defined as the elimination by an organism of the waste products that arise as a result of metabolic activity. These products include water, carbon dioxide (CO2), and nitrogenous compounds.
behavior is a type of multicellular organismal process.
feeding behavior is a type of behavior.

Biological process is a type of process defined as a specific objective that the organism is genetically programmed to achieve. These processes are often described by their outcome or ending state, for example, the biological process of cell division results in the creation of two daughter cells from a single parent cell. A biological process is accomplished by a particular set of molecular functions carried out by specific gene products (or macromolecular complexes), often in a highly regulated manner and in a particular temporal sequence. It has the exact synonyms "biological process" and "physiological process." Additionally, "single organism process" and "single-organism process" are related synonyms of a biological process.
metabolic process is a type of biological process.
biosynthetic process is a type of metabolic process.
aerobic respiration is a type of cellular respiration.
anaerobic respiration is a type of cellular respiration.
cellular process is a type of biological process.
methane metabolic process is a type of cellular alkane metabolic process.
Methanogenesis is a type of anaerobic respiration, methane metabolic process, energy derivation by oxidation of reduced inorganic compounds, and alkane biosynthetic process.
energy derivation by oxidation of reduced inorganic compounds is a type of generation of precursor metabolites and energy.
photosynthesis is a type of cellular metabolic process.
energy derivation by oxidation of organic compounds is a type of generation of precursor metabolites and energy.
Ammonia oxidation is a type of nitrogen compound metabolic process and also a type of small molecule metabolic process.

Anaerobic respiration using ammonium as an electron donor is a multifaceted process. It is a type of anaerobic respiration, energy derivation through the oxidation of reduced inorganic compounds, ammonia oxidation, and a cellular nitrogen compound metabolic process.

Aerobic respiration using nitrite as an electron donor is a type of aerobic respiration, a form of energy derivation by oxidation of reduced inorganic compounds, and a cellular nitrogen compound metabolic process.

Aerobic respiration using ammonia as the electron donor is a type of aerobic respiration, ammonia oxidation, and a cellular nitrogen compound metabolic process. Additionally, it is a means of deriving energy through the oxidation of reduced inorganic compounds.
Aerobic respiration using carbon monoxide as an electron donor is a type of aerobic respiration and also a method of energy derivation by oxidation of reduced inorganic compounds.
Aerobic respiration using ferrous ions as an electron donor is a type of aerobic respiration, as well as a form of energy derivation by oxidation of reduced inorganic compounds.
Aerobic respiration using hydrogen as an electron donor is a type of aerobic respiration and also a type of energy derivation by oxidation of reduced inorganic compounds.
Aerobic respiration that utilizes sulfur or sulfate as an electron donor is a form of aerobic respiration and also a method of energy derivation through the oxidation of reduced inorganic compounds.
The aerobic electron transport chain is a type of both aerobic respiration and respiratory electron transport chain.
electron transport chain is a type of generation of precursor metabolites and energy.
respiratory electron transport chain is a type of electron transport chain.

A multicellular organismal process is a category within biological processes. It is defined as any biological process that occurs at the level of a multicellular organism and is relevant to its function. This process is precisely synonymous with organismal physiological process and is also relatedly synonymous with single-multicellular organism process.
The cellular nitrogen compound metabolic process is both a type of nitrogen compound metabolic process and a type of cellular metabolic process.
eating behavior is a type of feeding behavior.
The cellular alkane metabolic process is a type of cellular metabolic process as well as a type of hydrocarbon metabolic process.
The alkane biosynthetic process is a type of cellular alkane metabolic process, cellular biosynthetic process, and hydrocarbon biosynthetic process.
Aerobic respiration using arsenite as an electron donor is a type of aerobic respiration and a method of energy derivation by oxidation of reduced inorganic compounds.
Cellular metabolic process is a type of metabolic process and also a type of cellular process.
The cellular biosynthetic process is a type of biosynthetic process, and it is also a type of cellular metabolic process.
small molecule metabolic process is a type of metabolic process.
cellular respiration is a type of energy derivation by oxidation of organic compounds.
organic substance metabolic process is a type of metabolic process.
The hydrocarbon biosynthetic process is a type of hydrocarbon metabolic process and also a type of organic substance biosynthetic process.
hydrocarbon metabolic process is a type of organic substance metabolic process.
The organic substance biosynthetic process is a type of biosynthetic process as well as a type of organic substance metabolic process.

Objective specification is a type of directive information entity and it is defined as a directive information entity that describes an intended process endpoint. When it is part of a plan specification, the concretization is realized in a planned process in which the bearer tries to effect the world so that the process endpoint is achieved.
Action specification is a type of directive information entity and it is defined as a directive information entity that describes an action the bearer will take.

A data item is a type of information content entity that is defined as an information content entity intended to be a truthful statement about something, considering factors like measurement precision or other systematic errors. It is constructed or acquired by a method that reliably tends to produce approximately truthful statements.
An information content entity is a type of generically dependent continuant, defined as a generically dependent continuant that is about some thing.

A scalar measurement datum is a type of measurement datum and is also a type of something that has at least 1 IAO 0000004. It is defined as a measurement datum that is composed of two parts: numerals and a unit label.
A directive information entity is a type of information content entity, defined as an information content entity whose concretizations indicate to their bearer how to realize them in a process.

A data set is a type of data item with the definition of being a data item that is an aggregate of other data items of the same type that have something in common. Averages and distributions can be determined for data sets.

An image is a type of figure. It is defined as an affine projection to a two-dimensional surface, of measurements of some quality of an entity or entities repeated at regular intervals across a spatial range. In this projection, the measurements are represented as color and luminosity on the projected surface.

A plan specification is a type of directive information entity characterized by two definitions that essentially convey the same information. It is defined as a directive information entity that includes action specifications and objective specifications as its parts. This entity, upon concretization, becomes a realizable entity. If realized, it manifests in a process wherein the bearer attempts to fulfill the objectives by undertaking the specified actions.
A measurement datum is a type of data item and is defined as an information content entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement, such as produced by a device.

A figure is a type of information content entity with a definition stating that it is an information content entity consisting of a two-dimensional arrangement of information content entities, in which the arrangement itself is about something.
time stamped measurement datum is a type of measurement datum.

A time-sampled measurement dataset is a type of dataset characterized by being an aggregate of data recording some measurement at a number of time points. Specifically, the time series dataset is defined as an ordered list of pairs, each consisting of time measurement data and the corresponding measurement data acquired at that time.
Root is a type of material entity and it has a related synonym, "all."
viruses is a type of organism.
obtectomera is a type of ditrysia.
mytiloidea is a type of mytilida.

        "Cyanophyta",
        "Oxygenic photosynthetic bacteria",
        "Oxyphotobacteria",
        "cyanobacteria" .
text: Cyanobacteria, a type of cyanobacteria belonging to the melainabacteria group, is exactly synonymous with blue-green algae, blue-green bacteria, and cyanophytes. Additionally, it has related synonyms including Cyanobacteriota, Cyanophyceae, Cyanophycota, Cyanophyta, Oxygenic photosynthetic bacteria, Oxyphotobacteria, and cyanobacteria itself.

oscillatoriaceae is a type of oscillatoriales.

pancrustacea is a type of mandibulata.
Mandibulata is a type of Arthropoda and has the exact synonym "mandibulates".
umezakia is a type of aphanizomenonaceae.

Bacteria is a type of cellular organism and also a type of organism. It has an exact synonym, eubacteria. Furthermore, bacteria is relatedly synonymous with Monera, Procaryotae, Prokaryota, Prokaryotae, bacteria, prokaryote, and prokaryotes.
Homininae is a type of Hominidae and is synonymously related to the Homo, Pan, and Gorilla group.
salicornia subgen amerocornia is a type of salicornia.
archaea is a type of organism.
hieroglyphus is a type of oxyinae.
Oedaleus is a type of Oedipodinae, and it also has a related synonym, Oedalus.
oxyinae is a type of acrididae.
Schizothrix is a type of Schizotrichaceae and has a related synonym, Dictyothrix.
ochrophyta is a type of stramenopiles.
spiralia is a type of protostomia.
Sar is a type of eukaryota, and it also has a related synonym SAR supergroup.
Oedipodinae, a type of Acrididae, is exactly synonymous with band-winged grasshoppers and is also relatedly synonymous with Locustinae.

Eukaryota is a type of cellular organisms and also a type of organism, which has the rank of NCBI taxon superkingdom. It has exact synonyms such as eucaryotes and eukaryotes. Additionally, Eukaryota has related synonyms including Eucarya, Eucaryotae, Eukarya, Eukaryotae, and eukaryotes.
autobranchia is a type of bivalvia.
lyngbya is a type of oscillatoriaceae.
conifers ii is a type of pinidae.

Bacillariophyta is a type of Ochrophyta and has exact synonyms such as Bacillariophytes and Diatoms. Moreover, it has related synonyms including Diatomea, Diatomeae, Diatomophyceae, and Algae, alongside being relatedly synonymous with Diatoms.

Dinophyceae, a type of Alveolata, is exactly synonymous with both dinoflagellates and dinophytes. Additionally, it has several related synonyms including Chromophyta, Dinoflagellata, Dinophycidae, Dinophyta, Pyrrhophyta, Pyrrophyta, algae, and again dinoflagellates.
pseudanabaenales is a type of cyanobacteria.
peridiniales is a type of dinophyceae.
modiolinae is a type of mytilidae.
mytilinae is a type of mytilidae.
euarchontoglires is a type of boreoeutheria.
Simiiformes, which is a type of Haplorrhini, has a related synonym known as Anthropoidea.
Hominoidea is a type of Catarrhini, and it has exact synonyms which are "ape" and "apes."
Embryophyta is a type of Streptophytina and has exact synonyms including higher plants, land plants, and plants. Moreover, Embryophyta has a related synonym, which is also land plants.
Tetrapoda is a type of Dipnotetrapodomorpha and it has the exact synonym "tetrapods".
Amniota is a type of Tetrapoda and it has the exact synonym "amniotes".
Theria mammals are a type of Mammalia and have the exact synonym "Theria."
Sauria is a type of Sauropsida and has an exact synonym, Diapsids. Additionally, it has a related synonym, Diapsida.

Viridiplantae, a type of eukaryota, is exactly synonymous with the Chlorophyta/Embryophyta group, chlorophyte/embryophyte group, and is also known as green plants. Additionally, it is relatedly synonymous with Chlorobionta, Chloroplastida, and is referred to as green plants as well.
Pinidae, which is a type of Pinopsida, has a related synonym known as Coniferales.
Opisthokonta is a type of Eukaryota, and it is also known by its related synonyms, the Fungi/Metazoa group and opisthokonts.
Metazoa is a type of Opisthokonta and has the exact synonyms metazoans and multicellular animals. Additionally, it has related synonyms Animalia and animals.
bilateria is a type of eumetazoa.
protostomia is a type of bilateria.
neoptera is a type of pterygota insects.

Endopterygota is a type of Neoptera and it also has a related synonym, Holometabola.
Deuterostomia, which is a type of Bilateria, is exactly synonymous with Deuterostomes.
Alveolata is a type of SAR and has the exact synonym "alveolates."
Stramenopiles is a type of SAR and has an exact synonym, heterokonts. Moreover, it has related synonyms including Chromophyta, Heterokonta, and Straminipila.
Cupressaceae, which is a type of Cupressales, has the exact synonym "cypress family" and is also relatedly known as Taxodiaceae.

Magnoliopsida, a type of Spermatophyta, is exactly synonymous with both angiosperms and flowering plants. Additionally, it is relatedly synonymous with Angiospermae, Magnoliophyta, and also referred to as flowering plants.
Caryophyllales is a type of Pentapetalae and has a related synonym, Centrospermae.
streptophyta is a type of viridiplantae.
Salicornia pacifica is a type of Salicornia under the subgenus Amerocornia, and it is also known by its related synonym Sarcocornia pacifica.
Brassicales, which is a type of Malvids, has a related synonym known as Capparales.
Cyrtacanthacridinae is a type of Acrididae and has exact synonyms including migratory bird locusts, spur-throated grasshoppers, and spur-throated locusts.
ditrysia is a type of heteroneura.
noctuoidea is a type of obtectomera.
haplorrhini is a type of primates.
Combretaceae, which is a type of Myrtales, also has the exact synonym "Indian almond family".
Modiolus is a type of Modiolinae and has the exact synonym "horsemussels".
pfiesteriaceae is a type of peridiniales.
Arecales is a type of commelinids and has a related synonym, Areciflorae.
Mammalia is a type of Amniota and has the exact synonym "mammals". Additionally, it has a related synonym also referred to as "mammals".
glossata is a type of lepidoptera.
neolepidoptera is a type of glossata.
heteroneura is a type of neolepidoptera.
avicennia is a type of avicennioideae.

lamiales is a type of lamiids.
acanthaceae is a type of lamiales.
Myrtales is a type of Malvids and it is also known by its related synonym, Myrtanae.
Dinosauria, which is a type of Archosauria, has the exact synonyms "dinosaur" and "dinosaurs."
saurischia is a type of dinosauria.
theropoda is a type of saurischia.
coelurosauria is a type of theropoda.
chortoicetes is a type of oedipodinae.
bataceae is a type of brassicales.
Batis eudicots is a type of Bataceae and has the exact synonym "Batis."
batis maritima is a type of batis eudicots.
Liliopsida is a type of Mesangiospermae, and it is exactly synonymous with monocots and monocotyledons. Additionally, it has related synonyms such as Monocotyledoneae and monocots.
Microcystis viridis is a type of microcystis and has a related synonym, Polycystis viridis.
Salicornia is a type of Salicornioideae and it has related synonyms, including Arthrocnemum and Sarcocornia.
calyptra is a type of erebinae.
Arecaceae, which is a type of Arecales, is also known exactly as Palmae, the palm family, and palms.
Commelinids is a type of Petrosaviidae and has related synonyms such as Commelinidae and Commeliniflorae.
Fungi is a type of Opisthokonta and has the rank of NCBI taxon kingdom. It has an exact synonym which is "fungi" itself, and related synonyms including "Mycota" and "fungi."
Insecta is a type of Hexapoda and has the exact synonym "true insects." Additionally, Insecta has a related synonym "insects."
Chortoicetes terminifera is a type of Chortoicetes and has the exact synonym Australian plague locust. Additionally, it has a related synonym Epacromia terminifera.
elaeis is a type of elaeidinae.
Elaeis guineensis is a type of Elaeis and it has the exact synonym "African oil palm."
Planktothrix is a type of Microcoleaceae and it has a related synonym, Oscillatoria sect. Prolificae.
Pinopsida is a type of Acrogymnospermae and it also has a related synonym known as Coniferopsida.
Tracheophyta is a type of Embryophyta and has both an exact synonym and a related synonym as vascular plants.
Spermatophyta is a type of Euphyllophyta and it has both an exact synonym and a related synonym, which are "seed plants."
eumetazoa is a type of metazoa.
Cnidaria is a type of eumetazoa, which has exact synonyms including cnidarians and coelenterates. Additionally, it has related synonyms such as Coelenterata and cnidarians.
Anthozoa is a type of Cnidaria and it has an exact synonym, Anthozoans. Additionally, Anthozoa has a related synonym, also referred to as Anthozoans.
Avicennioideae, which is a type of Acanthaceae, has a related synonym known as Avicenniaceae.
Mollusca is a type of Lophotrochozoa and it has exact synonyms such as molluscs and mollusks. Additionally, mollusca has a related synonym, molluscs.
Bivalvia is a type of Mollusca and has the exact synonym "bivalves." Additionally, it has related synonyms such as Lamellibranchiata, Pelecypoda, and bivalves.
Pteriomorphia is a type of Autobranchia and it is also known by its related synonym, Pteriomorpha.
Mytilida, which is a type of Pteriomorphia, also has a related synonym known as Mytiloida.
mytilidae is a type of mytiloidea.
mytilus is a type of mytilinae.
Arthropoda is a type of Panarthropoda and has the exact synonym "arthropods." Additionally, it has a related synonym also referred to as "arthropods."
erebidae is a type of noctuoidea.

A planned process is a type of process, defined as a process that realizes a plan, which is the concretization of a plan specification.
Processed material is a type of material entity that is defined as a material entity created or changed during material processing.

An environment control function is a type of function that has the definition of regulating a contained environment within specified parameter ranges, such as the control of light exposure, humidity, and temperature.

An organism is essentially the same as something that constitutes a union of viruses, bacteria, archaea, and eukaryota. It falls under the category of a material entity. The definition of an organism encompasses a material entity that represents an individual living system. This system could be an animal, plant, bacteria, or virus, each having the capability to replicate or reproduce, grow, and maintain itself under appropriate environmental conditions. Organisms may be unicellular or multicellular, with the latter comprising many billions of cells that are organized into specialized tissues and organs.
Quality is specifically a type of dependent continuant and is defined as a dependent entity that inheres in a bearer by virtue of how the bearer is related to other entities.

Speed is a type of movement quality and has the definition of a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's scalar absolute value of the rate of change of the bearer's position. Additionally, speed has a related synonym, velocity.
Age is a type of time and it is defined as a time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of how long the bearer has existed.

Color is a type of morphology and also a type of optical quality. It is defined as a composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation, and intensity parts. Furthermore, color has exact synonyms, including "colour" and "relative color."

Fluorescence is a type of luminous flux which is defined as a quality of luminous flux inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's emitting longer wavelength light following the absorption of shorter wavelength radiation. This phenomenon is common with aromatic compounds that have several rings joined together.
A color pattern is a specific kind of spatial pattern defined as a chromatic property that represents the relative position of different hues or degrees of saturation.

Composition is a type of structure. It is defined as a single physical entity inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's quantities or relative ratios of subparts. Composition has several exact synonyms, including "composed of," "compositionality," "content," and "structure, composition."

Concentration is a type of molecular quality and is defined as a quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the amount of the bearer's there is mixed with another substance. It also has the exact synonym "concentration."
Direction is a type of physical quality and is defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's orientation in space.
Frequency is a type of rate of occurrence and is defined as a physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the number of the bearer's repetitive actions in a particular time.

Hardness is a type of quality of a solid, defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resistance to pressure, being broken, or pierced. Additionally, hardness is related to the synonyms impenetrability and toughness.
Intensity is a type of qualitative and it is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's possessing or displaying a distinctive feature in type or degree or effect or force.
Morphology is a quality of physical objects, defined as a quality of a single physical entity that inheres in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's size, shape, or structure.

Shape is a type of morphology and has the definition "A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ratios of distances between its features (points, edges, surfaces, and also holes etc)." Additionally, shape has the exact synonym "relational shape quality."

Occurrence is a type of temporal distribution quality and is defined as a quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurrence. Additionally, occurrence has a broad synonym, temporal, and an exact synonym, incidence.
